  <gettingAround><![CDATA[<h3>Fantastic ferries</h3>
<p>The ferry network in Lake Garda is extremely useful. It's perfect for hopping from town to town around the lake and is a perfect if you want travel in style! Check out those sparkling waters as you drift along the lake. Many of our hotels are close to ferry landing points, so you won't have far to go. You'll find information on ferry timetables and prices on the <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.navigazionelaghi.it/risultati-di-ricerca/?lake=Garda" target="_blank" data-anchor="?lake=Garda">NaviGarda</a> website.</p>
<h3>Public transport</h3>
<p>There are lots of bus stops dotted around Limone. The bus network is really useful for exploring nearby towns such as Riva which takes around 25 minutes on the bus. The main ticket office is in Via IV Novembre but you can usually buy tickets in a nearby tabaccheria or on the bus itself.</p>]]></gettingAround>
