  <popularWalkingRoutes><![CDATA[<h3>Ciclopedonale Limone</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade:</strong> Easy with some uphill sections </li>
<li><strong>Distance:</strong> approx. 2 hours </li>
<li>Perfect photo point at Limonaia (old lemon greenhouses), where you can see Limone from afar as well as the lake and the mountains</li>
</ul>
<p><span>This walk begins from the Limone Centro Ferry Port, where you continue for around 30 minutes before reaching the start of the walk. The route can be travelled on by foot or bike. Part of the route overhangs the lake where you can enjoy breath-taking views suspended between the lake and the sky. Break up the walk with a gelato along the way.</span></p>
<h3>Cascata Di Sopino</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade:</strong> Moderate with some uphill sections </li>
<li><strong>Distance:</strong> 6 km</li>
<li>Gorgeous landscapes </li>
</ul>
<p><span>This walk begins from Nova Street, behind Hotel All'Azzurro. A real delight is when you reach the Sopino Waterfall with a 15 metre drop, it is a feast for the eyes. Along the hike, you'll pass gorgeous landscapes with lemon plantations and olive groves. </span></p>
<h3>Un Percorso Nella Natura - A Natural Trail</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade:</strong> Moderate</li>
<li><strong>Distance:</strong> 4.5km</li>
<li>Spot the local sight of the Statue Bridge ''San Giovanni''</li>
</ul>
<p>A route filled with pleasant rambles, varied terrain and uphill sections. Admire the amazing views of Lake Garda and the vegetation around Limone Sul Garda. The trail is well marked with maps showing where you are throughout. </p>
<h3>Limone &amp; the Singol Valley</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Grade:</strong> Very challenging</li>
<li><strong>Distance:</strong> 11km</li>
<li><strong>Ascent and descent:</strong> 700 metres </li>
<li><strong>Terrain:</strong> Asphalt surfaces, dirt tracks, natural trails, loose rocky terrain, narrow mountain paths, shere drops</li>
<li>Incredible views of Limone and the Singol Valley from above</li>
</ul>
<p>Starting from the centre of Limone the walk heads up alongside the San Giovanni torrent to the Dosso dei Roveri. The walk is a constant ascent from Limone up to the Dosso dei Roveri and has a fantastic panoramic viewpoint over Limone once you reach the top. You'll walk along a historical route which runs along a road built by the Italians during the First World War. This route isn't for the faint hearted but if you love a challenge and are desperate to get views of Limone right from the top then it's worth the effort!</p>
<h3>More great walking route inspiration</h3>
<p>You can view lots more recommended routes and maps on the <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.visitlimonesulgarda.com/en/trekking-limone-garda.htm#filter=r-fullyTranslatedLangus-,r-onlyOpened-,sb-sortedBy-0" target="_blank" data-anchor="#filter=r-fullyTranslatedLangus-,r-onlyOpened-,sb-sortedBy-0">Visit Limone Sul Garda</a> website<a rel="noopener" href="https://www.zermatt.ch/en/Media/Planning-hikes-tours" target="_blank">,</a> you can also see pictures of the routes and public transport options here.</p>]]></popularWalkingRoutes>
