  <thingsToDo><![CDATA[<h3>Traditional Italian Dining</h3>
<p>Limone is filled with traditional restaurants using the lemons that grow all around. There is an abundance of choice of traditional Italian cuisine to be enjoyed, whilst sitting back and enjoying the wonderful views Lake Garda has to offer. A perfect time to enjoy after a morning of hiking in Limone. </p>
<h3>Historical sights</h3>
<p>There’s lots of little nooks to explore in Limone. The Church of Saint Rocco is a hidden gem. We love visiting the oil mill for some tastings. Take a visit to Limonaia Del Castel to learn about the town’s history with the citrus fruit. Or take a visit the free tourist museum to learn why the residents in Limone live longer thanks to their genes. </p>
<h3>Enjoy local discounts and exploring Lake Garda</h3>
<p>Take advantage of the Garda Promotion Gard, available from your hotel. It's valid for three days and gives you special discounts and reduced rates for the ferries, museums, castles and other attractions. Limone’s not too far from <a data-udi="umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce" href="/{localLink:umb://document/89a5238595c34e53a5ef4c989b459fce}" title="Malcesine">Malcesine</a> so we recommend hopping onto a ferry and visiting the town. Make sure you head up Monte Baldo if you’re a fan of walking and great views! <a data-udi="umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01" href="/{localLink:umb://document/8bac09b5ee37405a9498e1494235fa01}" title="Riva">Riva</a> is easy to get to, too. You can also pre-book our Tour of Lake Garda excursion to see even more of the lake during your stay.</p>
<p> </p>]]></thingsToDo>
